parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the fuel filler pipe can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and safety hazards.
symptoms: Gasoline odors in the passenger compartment
fuel leaking from the vehicle
rust on the fuel filler pipe
corrosion of the fuel tank inlet pipe
fuel leaks onto the ground
stalling of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective fuel injector can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and safety hazards.
symptoms: Leakage at the middle seal of the fuel injector
smell of gasoline fumes inside the interior
fuel leaks onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel injection system can cause stalling of the engine, loss of power, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel injection system failed during acceleration in first and second gear
stalling of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Fuel Filler Pipe under Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair of the fuel filler pipe under recall can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and safety hazards.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the vehicle
corrosion of the fuel filler pipe
rust on the fuel filler pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to restrain the driver or passenger can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to hold the driver or passenger in place
the seat belt buckle unlatches prior to an accident
the seat belt does not lock
the seat belt is difficult to disconnect
the seat belt fails to secure the driver or passenger properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Recall Repairs for Seat Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs for seat belts can leave vehicles with faulty seat belts on the road, putting drivers and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Dealerships do not have parts available for recall repairs
owners are unable to schedule repairs despite receiving recall notices
multiple attempts to schedule repairs are unsuccessful.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Difficulty with Seat Belt Latching and Release Mechanism
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Difficulty with the seat belt latching and release mechanism can lead to improper use of the seat belt, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is difficult to latch
the seat belt buckle will not latch
the release mechanism won't unlatch
the seat belt is difficult to disconnect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped front disc brakes can cause vibration when applying the brakes, leading to reduced stopping power and increased stopping distance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibration coming from the vehicle when applying the brakes
stuttering or jerking sensation when stopping
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Difficulty stopping the vehicle
brakes fail to function properly
accident or near-miss due to brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake failure
difficulty stopping the vehicle
master cylinder replacement required.
